# ShadowCTX Personal Context

When the user references saved content, bookmarks, or prior research, use the `ctx` CLI to search their personal context store.

## Commands

```bash
# Semantic search (preferred)
ctx search "<query>" --json --limit 5

# List recent saves
ctx list --limit 10 --json

# Get full content
ctx get <id> --json

# Save a new page
ctx save <url> --tag <tag> --note "<note>"
```

## When to use

- User says "I saved", "I bookmarked", "check my context"
- Looking for information the user may have previously researched
- Any question where saved pages might provide useful grounding

## Setup requirements

Set in shell profile:
```
SUPABASE_URL=...
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=...
OPENAI_API_KEY=...   # enables semantic search
```

Install: `npm install -g shadowctx`
